## Task: Final Document Review and Targeted Improvements

Review the complete assembled HTML document and provide **targeted edit operations** to improve quality, structure, and academic integrity. Focus on issues that can only be addressed when viewing the complete document context.

### Priority Areas for Review

1. **Cross-Page Consistency**
   - Verify proper handling of elements that span multiple pages (tables, paragraphs, sections)
   - Check for orphaned table headers or caption misalignments
   - Ensure figure numbering and cross-references are consistent throughout
   - Validate that mathematical equation numbering flows properly

2. **Document Structure Integrity**
   - Verify logical heading hierarchy (no skipped levels like h2→h4)
   - Ensure proper nesting of sections and subsections
   - Check that the abstract, methodology, results, conclusion follow logical order
   - Validate bibliography and reference formatting consistency

3. **Academic Content Quality**
   - Review mathematical notation for completeness and accuracy
   - Check that all figures have proper captions and are referenced in text
   - Ensure tables maintain proper structure and alignment
   - Verify citation format consistency and completeness

4. **HTML Quality and Semantics**
   - Fix any malformed HTML or unclosed tags
   - Ensure proper semantic markup (article, section, figure, etc.)
   - Check accessibility attributes (alt text, table headers, etc.)
   - Remove any duplicate IDs or invalid markup

## Output Format: JSON Edit Operations

Provide your improvements as a JSON array of edit operations. Each operation should specify the exact text to find and replace. **Be extremely precise** with the old_text to ensure unique matches.

```json
{
  "edit_operations": [
    {
      "type": "replace",
      "description": "Fix heading hierarchy by changing h4 to h3",
      "old_text": "<h4 id=\"methodology-data-collection\">Data Collection Methods</h4>",
      "new_text": "<h3 id=\"methodology-data-collection\">Data Collection Methods</h3>"
    },
    {
      "type": "replace", 
      "description": "Complete partial table that was split across pages",
      "old_text": "</tr>\n<!-- TABLE_CONTINUES_ON_NEXT_PAGE --></table>\n<div class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"3\"></div>\n<!-- TABLE_CONTINUES_FROM_PREVIOUS_PAGE --><table>",
      "new_text": "</tr>"
    },
    {
      "type": "replace",
      "description": "Fix figure caption formatting and add missing reference",
      "old_text": "<figcaption>Results from the experiment</figcaption>",
      "new_text": "<figcaption><strong>Figure 2.1:</strong> Results from the experiment showing significant improvement in accuracy (p &lt; 0.05).</figcaption>"
    }
  ],
  "quality_assessment": {
    "overall_quality": "good|excellent|needs_improvement",
    "structural_issues_fixed": 3,
    "cross_page_issues_fixed": 1, 
    "academic_improvements": 2,
